-- Sanyo Shares Gain on Report It May Raise $341 Million Selling Chip Unit
-- Kyung Bok Cho
-- 2010-07-05T00:32:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/sanyo-rises-after-nikkei-report-it-plans-to-sell-semiconductor-operations.html

          
          
             Sanyo Electric Co. rose the most in
three weeks in Tokyo trading after the Nikkei English News
reported the Japanese electronics maker may sell its
semiconductor operations for as much as 30 billion yen.  
 Sanyo Electric advanced 2.6 percent to 117 yen as of 9:29
a.m. on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, headed for the biggest rise
since June 11. The benchmark Nikkei 225 Stock Average added 0.3
percent.  
          
          


  


        